parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A bent axle can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake at high speeds, leading to uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and potentially loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or vibrates at speeds of 40mph and higher
uneven tire wear
front end misalignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating of the rear end can cause premature wear on brake calipers, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear end overheating
brake calipers wear excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Gross Vehicle Weight Rating (GVWR) Exceeded
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exceeding the Gross Vehicle Weight Rating (GVWR) can lead to reduced vehicle stability, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents, particularly when driving on inclines or in adverse weather conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle's weight exceeds the manufacturer's specified GVWR
especially when fully loaded with camping gear
fuel
and other items
causing concerns about safety and stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Braking Performance with Excess Weight
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to brake properly, especially when carrying excess weight, can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and other property.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes overheat
the vehicle's stopping distance is increased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering difficulties, especially when carrying excess weight, can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and other property.
symptoms: The vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the vehicle's tires wear unevenly
the vehicle's steering system makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when towing or hauling heavy loads.
symptoms: The vehicle is hard to steer
the steering wheel feels heavy or stiff
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the power steering pump makes unusual noises
the power steering fluid level is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system while towing can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when towing or hauling heavy loads.
symptoms: The vehicle is hard to steer while towing
the steering wheel feels heavy or stiff while towing
the vehicle wanders or drifts while towing
the power steering pump makes unusual noises while towing.
